                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12894716" author="nspiegelberg" created="Mon, 2 Aug 2010 21:33:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch changes &quot;stop master&quot; to actually just stop the master and stop-hbase.sh should be the only &quot;quick command&quot; to stop the cluster.  Note that you can run bin/stop-hbase.sh on a unit that is not the master.  If not on the HMaster server, the script will not wait for the HMaster to stop before proceeding but should properly shutdown the system.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12894813" author="stack" created="Tue, 3 Aug 2010 04:24:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good stuff N.  Thanks for doing this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On bringing environment variables into stop-hbase.sh, could these instead be kept out in hbase-env.sh?  Isn&apos;t that sourced by this stop-hbase script?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let me know what you think on above.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(On commit, I&apos;ll go over the doc. to make sure we change how shutdown is done &amp;#8211; I&apos;ll do that, don&apos;t worry about it).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12894817" author="nspiegelberg" created="Tue, 3 Aug 2010 04:36:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The &apos;new&apos; evironment variables brought into stop-hbase.sh were brought in from hbase-daemon.sh.  They are to handle logging + pid watching, which was previously unique to hbase-daemon.sh.  I think if we get another file that needs the same pattern, we should abstract it out into a common bash file for handling process creation.  However, hbase-env.sh is not necessarily the proper place for that. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/help_16.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12895151" author="stack" created="Wed, 4 Aug 2010 05:31:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Nicolas OK on waiting till at least another file before abstracting out to a new shared sourced bash file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Committed.  Thanks for the patch N.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="15016755" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 12:40:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
